Two people died Monday night when a Machakos County ambulance collided with a matatu at Kathome on the Machakos-Nairobi road.Five others are admitted to hospital with serious injuries.The ambulance was rushing a sick child from Machakos to Kenyatta National Hospital when the crash occurred at around 11pm.The driver of the ambulance and a six-month-old baby died on the spot while the mother and a paramedic are admitted to Machakos Level 5 Hospital.Two other people, who were in the ambulance and the driver of the matatu are also being treated at the hospital.This is the second crash involving a Machakos County ambulance.On December 2 last year, two people died in a crash involving the county's ambulance on the Mwala-Machakos road.